The paper deals with developing a data structure for approximating order statistics of a large dataset with a certain error bound, which is a problem in data structures (cs.DS) and databases (cs.DB). The use of randomized algorithms and analysis of success probability suggest that the paper may also belong to the categories of computational complexity (cs.CC) and information theory (cs.IT). Lastly, the focus on space complexity and lower bounds suggests that the paper may also be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG).
